  44:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *
  45:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * Multiplies two matrices.
  46:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *
  47:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * @par Multiplication of two 3x3 matrices:
  48:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * 
  49:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \f[
  50:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \begin{pmatrix}
  51:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  a_{1,1} & a_{1,2} & a_{1,3} \\
  52:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  a_{2,1} & a_{2,2} & a_{2,3} \\
  53:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  a_{3,1} & a_{3,2} & a_{3,3} \\
  54:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \end{pmatrix}
  55:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * 
  56:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \begin{pmatrix}
  57:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  b_{1,1} & b_{1,2} & b_{1,3} \\
  58:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  b_{2,1} & b_{2,2} & b_{2,3} \\
  59:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  b_{3,1} & b_{3,2} & b_{3,3} \\
  60:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \end{pmatrix}
  61:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * =
  62:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \begin{pmatrix}
  63:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  a_{1,1} b_{1,1}+a_{1,2} b_{2,1}+a_{1,3} b_{3,1} & a_{1,1} b_{1,2}+a_{1,2} b_{2,2}+a_{1,3} b_{3,
  64:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  a_{2,1} b_{1,1}+a_{2,2} b_{2,1}+a_{2,3} b_{3,1} & a_{2,1} b_{1,2}+a_{2,2} b_{2,2}+a_{2,3} b_{3,
  65:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  *  a_{3,1} b_{1,1}+a_{3,2} b_{2,1}+a_{3,3} b_{3,1} & a_{3,1} b_{1,2}+a_{3,2} b_{2,2}+a_{3,3} b_{3,
  66:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \end{pmatrix}
  67:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * \f]
  68:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c **** 
  69:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * Matrix multiplication is only defined if the number of columns of the
  70:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * first matrix equals the number of rows of the second matrix.
  71:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * Multiplying an <code>M x N</code> matrix with an <code>N x P</code> matrix results
  72:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * in an <code>M x P</code> matrix.
  73:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * When matrix size checking is enabled, the functions check: (1) that the inner dimensions of
  74:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * <code>pSrcA</code> and <code>pSrcB</code> are equal; and (2) that the size of the output
  75:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  * matrix equals the outer dimensions of <code>pSrcA</code> and <code>pSrcB</code>.
  76:Drivers/CMSIS_DSP/Source/MatrixFunctions/arm_mat_mult_f32.c ****  */
